pullsbody: Dependency responsible for displaying pixel and collecting tracking data for GA. It's strongly related with mozilla/kuma#1985

This upgrades Django from 1.4.8 to 1.4.9, which takes us from insecure to merely outdated on requires.io

Changes mostly revolve around resolving some password length restriction issues that don't concern us anyway:

https://github.com/django/django/compare/6903d1690a92aa040adfb0c8eb37cf62e4206714...8f36d1fd952f5bc2066a8d33721025351bf2b4ce
Looks like the version we have didn't include migrations, and needed an upgrade from the official repo.

Although YUI compressor is old, it correctly parses media queries.

In the future we should use uglify but this is a good stop-gap.

pulltitle: Changed taggit to consider tag names case insensitive.

That is, after a tag has been created, all other case variations of the tag are considered references to the tag itself.
Also added some more tests and made sure that all tests pass.
